Place a #foil-lined baking sheet{} on top rack (for 4 servings, place 2 foil-lined
baking sheets on top and middle racks); preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim and halve
@Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1} until
you have 3 TBSP.

Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces; place in a large #pot{} with
enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender,
~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in empty pot over medium heat. Add scallion whites;
cook until softened, ~{1%minute}. Return potatoes to pot and mash with a
#potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, toss Brussels sprouts on one side of prepared #baking sheet{} with a
drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; arrange cut sides down. Add
@bacon{4%ounce} to empty side; season with salt and pepper. (For 4 servings, divide
between 2 baking sheets; roast Brussels sprouts on top rack and bacon on middle
rack.)

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from oven. Carefully sprinkle
bacon with @brown sugar{2%tablespoon}. Return to oven until bacon is crispy and
Brussels sprouts are tender, ~{10-15%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #stainless steel pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes}
per side.

During the last ~{2%minutes} of cooking, reduce heat to low and stir in
@garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} until melted; spoon over chicken until coated.
Turn off heat.

Leaving butter in pan, transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}.

== Pan Sauce ==

Add minced shallot to pan with reserved garlic herb butter. Cook over low heat
until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken demi-glace{1}, any resting juices from chicken, and ¼ cup
water. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in two packets @sour cream{6%tablespoon} (four packets for 4 servings; you'll
use the rest in the next step). Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Slice chicken crosswise. Chop bacon into small pieces.

Stir remaining sour cream into potatoes; add splashes of reserved potato cooking
liquid as needed until creamy.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and Brussels sprouts between plates. Top potatoes
and chicken with sauce. Garnish chicken with scallion greens and Brussels sprouts
with bacon. Sprinkle with @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste and serve.